FBIS4-4346 "dreas062_i_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-062 Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 Cambodia Khmer Rouge Captures Two T-54 Tanks 29 Mar Khmer Rouge Captures Two T-54 Tanks 29 Mar BK3103063694 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 30 Mar 94 BK3103063694 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia Cambodian BFN [Text] On 28 March, the National Army of Democratic Kampuchea [NADK], in cooperation with the people, launched a commando attack on the Sala Krau position, killing seven enemy soldiers and seizing seven AK assault rifles. The remaining enemy troops were forced to retreat into the jungle. On 29 March, the NADK attacked the 12th Division, which was temporarily stationed at Sala Krau. The fighting lasted five and a half hours. While the NADK was attacking the unit, four T-54 tanks and 200 ground troops were sent to help their companions. However, we killed 24 of them and wounded several others. We also burned two T-54 tanks, captured two others, and destroyed two military trucks. We also recaptured and reoccupied the summit of Srang Hill. We will continue to attack and destroy the remaining enemy troops at Sala Krau.
